+## Two-Strike Syntax Recovery Rule
+
+When the recent daemon failure context for the selected task includes two validation rollbacks caused by Python `SyntaxError`, `py_compile`, or TypeScript `TS1005`, `TS1109`, or `TS1128`, the next proposal must be a syntax-recovery proposal.
+
+A syntax-recovery proposal must:
+
+- edit the smallest possible file set, normally one file
+- avoid broad contract rewrites and avoid adding implementation modules unless the task explicitly requires them
+- use only complete file replacements
+- include no pseudo-code, placeholders, malformed comparisons, or mixed-language fragments
+- keep Python test files plain `unittest` files with helper functions and direct assertions
+- keep the changed Python file py_compile-safe before any broader unittest behavior is considered
+- stop after validating the committed fixture or adding the single requested mutation case
+
+If the task asks for a Python test repair, first mentally compile the replacement file. Reject the proposal and simplify it if any line would fail `python3 -m py_compile`.
 
